# FAAC TODO

## 1. High Priority: Audio Quality & Specialization (IoT/NVR/VoIP Focus)
- **Bit Reservoir Control**: Implement functional bit reservoir to allow stable bitrate distribution and provide extra bits for sharp transients.
- **CBR/ABR Bandwidth Capping**: Implement aggressive frequency bandwidth caps (3.5kHz - 5.5kHz) for low-bitrate encoding (<24kbps per channel) to eliminate metallic ringing.
- **Adaptive Quantization Rounding**: Implement tonality-aware magic number adjustment. Reduce bias from 0.4054 to ~0.30 for high-frequency noise-like bands to remove "metallic shimmer".
- **Short-block TNS (Temporal Noise Shaping)**: Enable and tune TNS for short blocks to suppress pre-echo artifacts in transient-heavy signals.

## 2. Medium Priority: Performance & Optimization
- **Fixed-point Transition**: Research transform-only hybrid fixed-point pipeline for extreme low-power embedded cores (e.g. Ingenic T31X/MIPS).
- **Trellis-based Huffman Pass**: Implement Trellis-based codebook selection to globally minimize bit cost.

## 3. Library Size Optimization
- **Modular Compilation**: Support disabling unused modules (DRM, TNS, PNS) via Meson to minimize binary footprint for memory-constrained devices.
- **Symbol Stripping & LTO**: Standardize Link-Time Optimization and symbol visibility for production IoT builds.

## 4. Low Priority: Compatibility & Maintenance
- **Resampler and Downmixer integration**: Official support for input preprocessing.
- **DRM Testing**: Comprehensive verification of Digital Radio Mondiale mode.
- **HE-AAC Support**: Spectral Band Replication (SBR) integration research.
- **Optimize CPE Windows Grouping**: Improve joint-channel coding gain.
